text.tspan: This is the Payments Landing page with the Filters open. Filers is accessible from the Payments Landing page when the
user selects the filter icon on the table control at the top right corner.
On this overlay, the user is able to filter through the list of payments on the landing page based on payment
Originating Account is the account that a payment was made from. This includes all current and past accounts the
OU has had. This will only display the accounts the user has authorization to.
Creation Date Range is a dropdown which the user can select predefined values, whereas the user can type in the
name of the recipient name, and amount range they are looking to filter. The user can also select any checkboxes to
Choosing the “Custom” option displays two date pickers for the user to enter a date range to filter by creation dates.
- From: [today’s date minus the maximum range available]

Clicking on ‘Clear all’ will unselect any selected checkboxes effectively returning to the default state of this overlay.
Clicking on ‘Cancel’ CTA, the user will close Filters and return back to the Recipients List overlay. There is no
confirmation of cancel for the filter overlay.
Once the user is satisfied with their filter selection, they can click on ‘Apply filter’ CTA to apply their selection to the
Payments Landing page. Upon selection, the filter is dismissed and the table will show only the rows that meet the
filter criteria specified by the user. as illustrated in “1.6.4.4 Payment Landing Page - Filters Applied”.

If there are no matching results the modal is dismissed and a message is displayed on the Activity list as illustrated
in “1.6.4.3 Payment Landing Page - Filter - No Matching Results”.
Filter errors are discussed in “1.6.4.1 Payment Landing Page - Filter - Validation Errors”.
